The project aims to develop girls and young women to become responsible citizens of the world. Through the exchange project, young women will live abroad and take part in advocacy work for climate change and deliver menstrual health hygiene education. When the participants return to their home organsiations, they will use the knowledge and skills acquired to develop their own organisations.

The Exchange project will work for the development of robust private sector enterprises in rural livelihoods. The participants will share knowledge, experience and skills from countries in Asia and Africa. Priority sectors will be Renewable Energy Technologies, Agriculture and Tourism.
The risks from landmines, cluster munitions and other explosive weapons are reduced to a level where civilians can live in safety and development is not constrained.
